<h2>
How to convert the coordinates in decimals degrees?
</h2>

<ul>
    <li>
    You can use <a href="http://postgis.refractions.net/">PostGIS</a> if your data is in a PostgreSQL Database.
    Here is an example of request :<br/>
    <pre>
    SELECT ST_X(g) AS x, ST_Y(g) AS y
    FROM (
    	SELECT ST_Transform(ST_GeomFromText('POINT ('|| X || ' ' || Y || ')', myESPGCODE), 4326) AS g
    ) AS req;
    </pre>
    </li> 
    
    <li>
    You can use the <a href="http://trac.osgeo.org/proj/">PROJ</a> library to convert coordinates (see <a href="http://pwet.fr/man/linux/commandes/cs2cs">cs2cs manual</a>).
    </li>
    
    <li>
    You can also use an open-source SIG like <a href="http://earth-info.nga.mil/GandG/geotrans/">GEOTRANS</a>, <a href="http://udig.refractions.net/">uDig</a> <a href="http://www.qgis.org/">Quantum GIS</a> or <a href="http://www.gvsig.gva.es/">gvSIG</a>
    </li>
</ul>


<h2>
I have the error message "Wrong column number" when uploading data.
</h2>
<p>
The last column is often cut by Excel, as this last column is a comment, you can add some text (for example "-") to force Excel to generate the column.
</p>


